    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Bubon galbaniferum are its anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antispasmodic properties. Its ability to reduce inflammation is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and terpenoids, which exhibit a strong inhibitory effect on pro-inflammatory enzymes. The antimicrobial properties of Bubon galbaniferum are due to the presence of saponins and phenolic compounds, which exhibit a broad-spectrum of activity against various microorganisms. The antispasmodic properties of this plant are attributed to the presence of volatile oils, which exhibit a relaxing effect on smooth muscle. Additionally, Bubon galbaniferum has been found to exhibit antioxidant and hepatoprotective properties, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids.",
