    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Bubon galbaniferum are galbanic acid, sesquiterpene lactones such as galbanolide, and alkaloids including galbanine and buxine. These compounds have been found to possess anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antispasmodic properties. Galbanic acid has been shown to have antioxidant activity, while sesquiterpene lactones have been found to inhibit the growth of certain bacteria and fungi. The alkaloids present in Bubon galbaniferum have been reported to have a sedative effect, making it useful for treating anxiety and insomnia. The combination of these constituents contributes to the plant's reputation for treating a variety of ailments, including fever, rheumatism, and respiratory issues.",
