    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Bubon galbaniferum are galbanum oil, galbanum tincture, galbanum infusion, galbanum salve, and galbanum cream. Galbanum oil is obtained through steam distillation of the plant's resin, used in aromatherapy for its calming and anti-inflammatory properties. Galbanum tincture is made by soaking the plant's roots and rhizome in a solvent, commonly used in traditional medicine for its expectorant and anti-spasmodic effects. Galbanum infusion is a herbal tea prepared by steeping the plant's leaves and flowers in hot water, traditionally used to treat respiratory issues and digestive problems. Galbanum salve and cream are topical preparations used to treat skin conditions such as eczema, acne, and wounds due to their antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties.",
