    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effect of using Bubon galbaniferum are experiences nausea, experiences vomiting, develops allergic reactions, experiencing dizziness, and in severe cases, can cause respiratory depression. Bubon galbaniferum is a plant-based remedy that contains a compound called furanocoumarin, which can cause adverse effects when ingested improperly. These side effects occur due to the compound's ability to interact with enzymes in the liver, resulting in an increased risk of nausea, vomiting, and allergic reactions. Dizziness may also be caused by the rapid release of furanocoumarin into the bloodstream, leading to a drop in blood pressure. Ingesting Bubon galbaniferum improperly can lead to serious health complications, including organ damage and even death.",
